      "id": "mcq-1",
      "question": "Which is NOT a valid kernel function?",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "Linear: K(x,y) = x\u00b7y"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "Polynomial: K(x,y) = (x\u00b7y + 1)^d"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "Sigmoid: K(x,y) = tanh(ax\u00b7y + b)"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "Exponential: K(x,y) = e^(-||x-y||)"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "D",
      "explanation": "Exponential kernel isn't standard. RBF uses squared norm: exp(-\u03b3||x-y||\u00b2)",
      "difficulty": "medium"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-2",
      "question": "The SVM optimization objective minimizes:",
